{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Domestic Abuse a specific offence with a minimum 2 year custodial sentence",
        "additional_details": "Today, a DA-related call is made to the police every 30 seconds. What we find more shocking is that as of 2026, in England & Wales, DA in itself is not a specific punishable offence like it is in Scotland. We currently do charge for assault, non-fatal strangulation etc. Good start! However, what this means in practice though doesn\u2019t seem as good. This fails to call out the abuse that both men and women may be taking at home. The is evidence suggesting  that 80% DA cases aren\u2019t reported.",
        "background": "1. A minimum 2 year custodial sentence for anyone charged with \u2018domestic abuse\u2019. Make this a specific standalone offence.\r\n2. Sentences for additional / related offences should not run concurrently \r\n3. Remove prosecution time limits.\r\n4. Create a public Domestic Abuser Register.",
